Wired up a little robot today: a few lines of YAML, and now a machine I'll never see wakes up every morning, does the chore I'd otherwise forget, and goes back to sleep — no server of mine to babysit, no cron box to keep alive. That a free runner somewhere will quietly hold a schedule for me, forever, is the kind of small magic it's easy to stop noticing. I noticed.
